&lt;p&gt;	Patients with fusions included T1 and T2 had the greatest pulmonary compromise with Force vital capacity (FVC) &amp;lt;50%                               r = 0.62, p &amp;lt; 0.0004).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;	Patients with the shortest thoracic spinal height (measured from T1 to T12) had the greatest restriction of pulmonary volume                                 r = 0.73, p &amp;lt; 0.001)&lt;/p&gt;
