&lt;p&gt;In patients with scoliosis:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•	forced expiratory volume in one second was only 27 % of normal values&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•	It also diminished maximum inspiratory pressure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•	Caused chest weakness and hypercarbia&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Figures source:&lt;/p&gt;
